# Decision Escalation Checkpoints

Use this rule to avoid silent scope drift during autonomous implementation.

## Must pause and ask before proceeding when:

- feature scope changes (new/removed requirements)
- user-visible UX/flow changes from prior intent
- database schema or migration strategy changes
- auth/security behavior changes (token/session/permissions)
- deployment/runtime strategy changes
- significant timeline/risk increase is discovered

## Response style

- State what changed.
- Provide 1-3 options.
- Recommend one option with a short reason.
- Wait for confirmation before implementing high-impact choice.

## Continue without interruption when:

- refactors are internal only
- naming/organization changes do not alter behavior
- low-risk implementation details change while preserving agreed outcomes
